  "why": "The paper designs mutation operators that explicitly aim to preserve semantic correctness and naturalness at each mutation step (they use LLM-assisted Generate/Crossover/Expand/Shorten/Rephrase operators and state these preserve overall meaning). However, the fuzzer does not describe any mechanism that enforces semantic similarity relative to the original seed across multiple iterations or that bounds cumulative distortion (instead it relies on per-step LLM-guided mutations and a reward oracle that detects harmful outputs). Thus the system enforces semantic consistency and naturalness between successive mutation steps but does not account for potential drift accumulated over repeated mutations, matching the definition of Medium.",
